  "text": "displaying Σ ∞ X τ + as a module over the motivic ring spectrum Σ ∞ P ∞ + . (We defer the somewhat technical definition of this module structure to Section 3.) When S is a smooth scheme over a field we can identify the homotopy classes of maps from X to BBG m with the third integral motivic cohomology group MZ 3,1 (X ) of weight one. This group is in fact trivial for smooth schemes of finite type over S by [CITATION_1] Corollary 3.2.1] . On the other hand, it is nontrivial for motivic spheres.",
